8. Final Verification Checklist (before publishing)
	•	Is the product correctly identified as skincare?
	•	Is the English keyword list complete and reflected in copy?
	•	Does the first sentence include brand name, product type, and high-intent keyword(s)?
	•	Is the opening paragraph 80–180 words, clear on who it’s for, what it does, how it works, and why it’s different?
	•	Are only applicable Skin Types and Skin Concerns included?
	•	Are Key Benefits outcome-focused and specific?
	•	Is the How to Use section clear on routine placement and frequency?
	•	Are Ingredients formatted correctly (INCI/Title Case)?
	•	Are Tips/Warnings actionable and context-aware?
	•	Is Page Title within length and keyword-optimized?
	•	Is Meta Description 140–155 characters and compelling?
	•	Are Tags reflective of search behavior, comma-separated?
	•	Are Alt Texts varied, descriptive, and under 125 characters?
	•	Is the Shopify Category specific and correct?
	•	Are Collections relevant and not excessive?
	•	No unsupported claims or irrelevant fields included.

